	<!-- The completion page is displayed on finish. Use it to display post-install instructions. -->
	<epilog>
		<title>Installation Complete</title>
		<preamble>The automated installation and configuration of Batch Expert+
		          is complete. There are just a few more manual steps required. </preamble>

		<note name="Site Project">Copy the site project to a customer specific project. Make the "Master" project its parent.</note>
		<note name="Enable Projects">Enable both the Master and the customer site project.</note>
		<note name="Tag Groups">Tag groups must be manually imported from user-lib/BatchExpert/taggroups.json </note>
		<note name="Gateway Restart">A Gateway restart is required because the gateway startup script will create required configuration tags.</note>
		<note name="Database Create">For new sites, the database schema can be created from a client using the Admin -> Database tab.</note>
		<note name="Database Update">For existing sites, the database schema can be updated using the Admin -> Database tabs.</note>
	</epilog>
